    en:{ title:'Project 2 – Editing & Proofreading: Annual Report', body:`<h3>Project 2 – Editing & Proofreading: Annual Report</h3>

<p><strong>Client:</strong> BrightPath Energy  
<strong>Deliverable:</strong> Line-edited excerpt + style guide  
<strong>Skill:</strong> Editing & proofreading — Annual report</p>

<h4>Edited Excerpt (Original → Final)</h4>

<p><strong>Original text (as received from client):</strong></p>

<blockquote>
<em>“The company has made significant strides in solar deployment across three continents, which is something we are very proud of as a leadership team. It should be noted that supply chain disruptions affected timelines in certain regions, but nevertheless we achieved a lot. Our wind energy capacity is now at 1.2 gigawatts, and we’re also happy to report that our battery storage projects have grown quite a bit.”</em>
</blockquote>

<p><strong>Final edited version (with changes explained):</strong></p>

<blockquote>
BrightPath deployed <strong>340 MW</strong> of new solar capacity across three continents — a <strong>47% increase</strong> from 2023. ^(1)
<br>
Supply chain disruptions delayed four projects by an average of 22 days. ^(2) Despite these delays, wind energy capacity reached 1.2 GW, and battery storage grew by 210 MWh (31% year‑over‑year). ^(3)
</blockquote>

<h5>Editor’s notes:</h5>

<ol>
<li><em>“Significant strides”</em> → replaced with specific data (340 MW, +47%). Removed subjective “very proud.”</li>
<li>Passive voice <em>“It should be noted that…”</em> → active: <em>“Supply chain disruptions delayed…”</em> Added specific count (four projects) and average delay (22 days).</li>
<li><em>“We achieved a lot”</em> → deleted (vague). <em>“Happy to report”</em> → deleted (unprofessional). <em>“Quite a bit”</em> → replaced with exact figure (210 MWh, 31%).</li>
</ol>

<h4>BrightPath Energy – Annual Report Style Guide (2024)</h4>

<table>
<tr><th>Rule Category</th><th>Specification</th></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Numbers</strong></td><td>Numerals for ≥10; percentages with % symbol; one decimal place</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Dates</strong></td><td>Q1, Q2, Q3, Q4; spell months; four‑digit years</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Voice</strong></td><td>Active voice; remove “quite/very/rather/somewhat”</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Terminology</strong></td><td>solar facilities (not farms); wind turbines; renewable energy (not clean)</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Punctuation</strong></td><td>Oxford comma; em dashes with spaces; no semicolons in bullets</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Corporate name</strong></td><td>“company” lowercase (unless starting a sentence)</td></tr>
</table>

<h5>Sample proofreading corrections:</h5>

<table>
<tr><th>Original error</th><th>Correction</th></tr>
<tr><td>“the Company’s assets”</td><td>“the company’s assets”</td></tr>
<tr><td>“its’ portfolio”</td><td>“its portfolio”</td></tr>
<tr><td>“affecting 3 project’s”</td><td>“affecting three projects”</td></tr>
</table>`},
